entry.title: Add encryption info to ArchiveAnalyzerResults
entry.content:
This is used to validate the password provided for an archive. Since we

currently don't support AES encryption for ZIPs, we have three possible

outcomes for passwords:

- Known correct (archive unpacks successfully)

- Known incorrect (archive fails to unpack with this password)

- Unknown (AES encryption)



We also provide is_encrypted in this field, since RAR unpacking will one

day support detection of metadata encryption, which is not currently

reflected anywhere else in the ArchiveAnalyzerResults

entry.title: [GTK] Fix invalid type-class reference in GTK4
entry.content:
The `g_type_class_ref` hack was added to prevent the compiler from

optimizing away `g_type` so that libgtk.so would be identical

when built with GTK3 or GTK4. However, this is

1. Not necessary for correctness

2. Causes log-spam when the type is not convertable to a

type-class (which can happen with GdkPaintable on GTK4

for reasons I don't understand).

Now that it's recommended to use CHECK() instead of DCHECK() when

possible, this CL removes `g_type_class_ref` and replaces with

CHECK().

entry.title: Automatically annotate dangling ExperimentalAsh pointers [6/N]
entry.content:
This patch is:

- Automated. See [automation] section.

- Not affecting users, only Chrome's CQ. See [no-op] section.



This is a split affecting:

- components/



Context:

--------

@bartekn is going to remove the `ExperimentalAsh` raw_ptr annotation.

This was a performance experiment to enable/disable MiraclePtr on a

subset of new pointers added for ChromeOS ash (non-lacros).



Before removing it, he needs to enable it by default in code. Enabling

MiraclePtr for them, causes the DanglingPointerDetector to be enforced.

To pass the CQ, we need to annotate pre-existing dangling pointer with

`DanglingUntriaged`. After enabling ExperimentalAsh feature, it won't be

allowed anymore for those pointers to become dangling.



Automation:

-----------

1. Enable the `PartitionAllocBackupRefPtrForAsh` feature flag.

2. Apply the 'annotator' CL: https://chromium-review.googlesource.com/c/chromium/src/+/4474553

3. Run all the gtests. See https://docs.google.com/document/d/1AMMERcqy0eafFWopUCHYsIKIKEp3J8DFxqW9UIbzIHo

4. Concatenate all the output_*, `filter`, `sort -nr`, `uniq`.

5. Run https://github.com/ArthurSonzogni/chrome-dangling-ptr-apply-edit

6. Run `git cl format`

7. Cherry-pick the patch created from (5)



no-op:

------

The DanglingPointerDetector is not enabled against users. It only

affects tests and chromium developers.

entry.title: Run InitializeCommandLine for subclasses of TestSuite
entry.content:
base::PerfTestSuite::InitializeCommandLine was never called because the

base class called the virtual method from the constructor while the

vtable still pointed to the base class version of the method. This meant

that benchmark command-line options such as `--benchmark_filter` were

never applied.



Restructure base::TestSuite to call InitializeCommandLine() from within

Initialize(). This means that the constructor arguments need to be

stored within the object so that they can be used during Initialize()

later.



base::CommandLine::Init() is now called from PreInitialize() during

construction as base::CommandLine needs to be initialized before Run()

is called.



Also, move the `initialized_command_line_` bool in the TestSuite object

to avoid having a gap in the object layout.

> Add DXC DLLs to Chrome installer

> This adds 2 files, dxcompiler.dll and dxil.dll, to the installer if

> GN arg `dawn_use_built_dxc` is true.

>

> * dxcompiler.dll is the core DXC library, and is built from source by

> Dawn when `dawn_use_built_dxc` is true (currently false for Chrome).

>

> * dxil.dll is Microsoft's DXIL signing DLL. When `dawn_use_built_dxc`

> is true, the latest version of this file is copied from the platform

entry.title: [CVV Storage] Fix UpdateCreditCard with no CVC set initially
entry.content:
Insert CVC if it doesn't exist, and update CVC if it exists



Problem:

User have a existing card without CVC, then user update the card with a first CVC, Chrome will crash.



Cause:

When user update a credit card with or without new CVC, UpdateCreditCard function will be called and UpdateBuilder kLocalStoredCvcTable will be triggered.

Since kLocalStoredCvcTable is empty because user never trigger InsertBuilder kLocalStoredCvcTable, triggering UpdateBuilder kLocalStoredCvcTable will make chrome crash.

platform authenticators (i.e. the profile authenticator and iCloud

entry.title: Avoid R8 EGLImages on Mali GPUs with Android <= 9
entry.content:
R8 EGLImage siblings cannot be rendered to or have data uploaded

to them on some Mali devices. The validating command decoder works

around this limitation by directly sharing the source texture for

the EGLImage but the passthrough command decoder cannot because full

cross-context and cross-thread usage of the EGLImages is needed for

DrDC.



Instead, fall back to L8 textures for video decoding. The video

pipeline will still be entirely on the GPU but drivers may need to do

internal workarounds and emulation to support luminance textures.

entry.title: Automatically annotate dangling ExperimentalAsh pointers [8/N]
entry.content:
This patch is:

- Automated. See [automation] section.

- Not affecting users, only Chrome's CQ. See [no-op] section.



This is a split affecting:

- chrome/browser/ash/

- chrome/browser/chromeos/

- chrome/browser/ui/ash/



Context:

--------

@bartekn is going to remove the `ExperimentalAsh` raw_ptr annotation.

This was a performance experiment to enable/disable MiraclePtr on a

subset of new pointers added for ChromeOS ash (non-lacros).



Before removing it, he needs to enable it by default in code. Enabling

MiraclePtr for them, causes the DanglingPointerDetector to be enforced.

To pass the CQ, we need to annotate pre-existing dangling pointer with

`DanglingUntriaged`. After enabling ExperimentalAsh feature, it won't be

allowed anymore for those pointers to become dangling.



Automation:

-----------

1. Enable the `PartitionAllocBackupRefPtrForAsh` feature flag.

2. Apply the 'annotator' CL: https://chromium-review.googlesource.com/c/chromium/src/+/4474553

3. Run all the gtests. See https://docs.google.com/document/d/1AMMERcqy0eafFWopUCHYsIKIKEp3J8DFxqW9UIbzIHo

4. Concatenate all the output_*, `filter`, `sort -nr`, `uniq`.

5. Run https://github.com/ArthurSonzogni/chrome-dangling-ptr-apply-edit

6. Run `git cl format`

7. Cherry-pick the patch created from (5)



no-op:

------

The DanglingPointerDetector is not enabled against users. It only

affects tests and chromium developers.
